    "description": {
      "value": "<p>The discipline of Golden Lion is a practice passed between war leaders, chieftains, generals, and militia leaders over the generations, meant to bring a group of warriors together into one cohesive unit. Golden Lion is a discipline that only greatly benefits a warrior who believes strongly in teamwork. The larger the group, the more who can benefit from the skilled leadership of a dedicated commander. Golden Lion benefits its practitioners indirectly, by aiding their allies instead.</p><p><strong>Associated Skills</strong>: Diplomacy </p><p><strong>Associated Weapon Groups</strong>: Heavy blades, hammers, and pole arms  </p>",
